<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Poland (
                        Griffis
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d195</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">195</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-07-10T09:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-07-10T09:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-10T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/7–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Griffis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-10T16:00:00+02:00">July 10, 1947—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1092. Continuing my 1089 July 10.<note n="1" xml:id="d195fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> In reference to sudden change in Polish
                    plans to send delegation Paris conference it is my distinct and firm impression
                    that Foreign Minister was honest in statement on Monday that delegation would
                    attend and again my firm impression last night that he himself if not entire
                    Polish Cabinet had in the interim been overruled by higher authority. His
                    attitude extremely apologetic and at least apparently regretful.</p>
                <p>If Department has any desire receive Polish plan for reconstruction referred to
                    1089 please advise.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept; repeated Paris 155, London 112.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Griffis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
